      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "GOLD HARADA (4) had a tricky draw last time and although midfield in fourth wasn't far away finishing 5 lengths from the winner (22.41). Form here at the trip sound including three wins. Comes out of a solid form race last start. Should bounce back. HOOKED ON GIN (2) stalked the lead from a low draw and fought on well to finish 5 lengths back in third (28.55) at Bendigo in a Bottom Up - Grade 5 over 500m. Winning chance. PAW VARNER (1) was responsible for a modest effort most recently when seventh at Bendigo over 425m behind Fluent Action (24.89) in a Grade 5. Better than the latest run and deserves another chance. PAW RAZOR (5) was in the money again last time and not beaten far when second (22.23) at Ballarat in a Grade 5.",
